text: The Jadgal people are an Indo-Aryan Sindhi community, which live in Pakistan and Iran, they are also found in Oman, UAE where they are called as Al Zadjali. The Jadgal people speak the Jadgali language. The population of Jadgal people living in Pakistan was at about 100,000 in 1998. Jadgal people are Muslims. == References == Category:Ethnic groups in Iran Category:Ethnic groups in Pakistan
